RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRIGADE COMMANDER tracked in the three to two path, ranged up three wide around the far turn to take aim on the leader entering the lane, sustained a bid in midstretch, then flopped back to his left lead in the final furlong and edged ahead. ATHENS MOON set the pace along the inside with a low head-carriage, held sway through upper stretch, resisted the eventual winner's bid in midstretch but was bested late. MISSIONAIRE saved ground off of the pace, tipped three wide and between horses entering the lane, then split foes through narrow quarters at the furlong grounds to edge show. NOW THAT ICAN ROCK laid off of the pace three wide, inched closer four wide around the far turn, vied for show with an inner rival through midstretch but was outkicked by an inner bidder at the sixteenth pole. ROYAL SALUTE saved ground in midpack, advanced three wide and between horses entering the lane, vied for show with an outer rival coming to midstretch, but was bested by a foe-splitting rival for that position. GIVEN TO FLY (IRE) laid off of the pace two wide and between horses, took the far turn in the four path and lacked a bid. ABSOLUTELY CERTAIN was taken up soon after the start, raced at the rear three wide, got hung five wide around the far turn, then moved up. ELEGANT TRIP bumped an inner rival at the start, pursued from midpack two wide and between horses, but gave way around the far turn. HOGSLAYERS R I P bumped with an outer rival at the start, raced forwardly while keen moving past the wire for the first time, brushed an outer foe causing a brief steady into the first turn, settled into stalking stride along the inside around that bend, but weakened through the lane. ROYAL SANDRIN broke a beat slow, raced at the rear two wide and between horses, bumped an inner rival turning for home and made little impact. ORBI ONE took contact from rivals on both sides at the start, raced forwardly two wide, took contact from an inner rival entering the first turn, stalked two wide before chasing between horses around the far turn, and weakened. METALLURGIC lacked speed along the inside, took contact from an outer rival and was forced to brush the rail turning for home, then got outrun thereafter.
